The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Homicide charge for fatal crash 
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Homicide charge for fatal crash 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A case of culpable homicide not amounting to murder has been started against the driver of the Tata Indica that rammed into a truck near the main gate of Fort William on Saturday night, killing three teenaged school students.        
	The car in which the three were travelling jumped to the wrong flank of the road and collided head-on with a truck. Abhijit Ganguly, who was behind the wheel, has been arrested under Section 304 of the IPC, said an officer of Maidan police station.         
	The 26-year-old was drunk and driving at breakneck speed when he lost control of the car, according to the police.        
	The mishap killed Sunil Hela, 18, Amit Das, 19, and Rahul Das, 18. Abhijit and Jitendra Hela, 18, sustained injuries and were admitted to NRS Hospital.        
	The condition of Abhijit and Jitendra is stable now. Abhijit will be arrested and produced in Alipore court, added the officer.         
	A probe revealed that the car belonged to a trader in central Calcutta. Abhijit had been working as a driver for him for a year.        
	He was known to the four students  all of them residents of Moulali  and took them for a joyride on Saturday night.        
	Jitendra, a Class XII student of Collins School, who lives in the Group D quarters of NRS Medical College and Hospital, said the five had assembled at Santosh Mitra Square around 8pm for the ride. Jitendras father works as a sweeper in the hospital.                                                                                                                                                           
